    "body": "PDF exports Web reports are great for sharing online, but sometimes you need a file — something to print, mail, attach to an email, or hand to your board. The PDF Builder is Storyraise's dedicated tool for designing and exporting polished, print-ready PDF documents. Opening the PDF Builder From the dashboard, find the Advanced PDF Builder card under tools and click Continue . The PDF Builder opens in a new tab, where you'll see your recent documents and can create a new one. Setting up a document When you create a document, you'll pick a page size and set up brand basics. You can change any of these later from the document title in the menu bar: Format — US Letter, US Legal, Tabloid, A3, A4, A5, Square, 5×7, 4×6 postcard, or custom dimensions in inches or millimeters. Orientation — portrait or landscape. Brand fonts — upload your own font files (.woff, .woff2, .ttf, or .otf) to use as defaults for headings and body text. Logo and colors — set your logo and brand colors so they're at hand while you design. Designing pages Build each page by dragging items from the Insert panel onto the canvas — text, images, and other widgets — then fine-tune them in the Styles tab. Right-click any widget to duplicate it, lock it in place, reorder it (bring to front / send to back), or delete it. Pages can be organized into chapters as your document grows. Print-shop options If you're sending your PDF to a professional printer, the PDF Builder includes the production settings they'll ask for: Safe-area margin — keeps important content away from the page edge. Bleed — extends backgrounds past the trim edge (none, ⅛\", or ¼\"). Crop marks — printed guides showing where pages will be trimmed (available when bleed is on). Page numbers — toggle Show page numbers in PDF and pick a format ( 1 or 1 / 12 ). For a PDF you'll only share digitally, you can leave bleed and crop marks off. Exporting When your document is ready, open the menu bar and click Export PDF . Your browser downloads the finished PDF — fonts, images, and page numbers included. Tips Design for the destination. Pick your page size before you design — switching sizes later can shift your layouts. Use real fonts. Uploading your brand's actual font files ensures the exported PDF matches your printed materials exactly. Proof before printing. Print one copy from your own printer to check margins and colors before sending a large run to a print shop."
